FBIS4-37954 "drnes123_j_94011" FBIS-NES-94-123 Daily Report 26 Jun 1994 Arabian Peninsula Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden Further Reportage on Fighting Around Aden 16 Killed, 45 Wounded in Aden 26 Jun NC2606134394 Paris AFP in English 1302 GMT 26 Jun 94 NC2606134394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Aden, Yemen, June 26 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni forces killed 16 civilians, including four children, and wounded 45 in heavy shelling of the southern port city of Aden Sunday [26 June], hospital workers said here. The four children died when Katyusha rockets slammed into the al-Tawahi district near the port. Twenty civilians were wounded in the same attack, workers at the Basuhayb military hospital said. One of the rockets damaged a house and another exploded near a school sheltering displaced people. Earlier workers at the Al-Jumhuriyah hospital said 12 dead civilians and 25 wounded had been admitted during the bombardment Sunday. Fierce fighting resumed at dawn, shattering a ceasefire announced by the Sanaa authorities, and northern troops advanced into the western suburbs, seizing the Hiswah power station and Radio Aden buildings on the coast road.
